        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 2 at 6:04PM CDT until June 2 at 6:30PM CDT by NWS Sioux Falls SD</headline>
        <description>At 604 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Elk Point, or
11 miles north of Ponca, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
considerable tree damage. Wind damage is also likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

This severe storm will be near...
Akron and Jefferson around 610 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this severe thunderstorm include
Hinton.
</description>
        <instruction>Prepare immediately for large hail and damaging winds. People outside
should move to a shelter, inside a strong building and away from
windows.</instruction>
